# Navigate to your FSIPD directory
cd D:\FSIPD
```

2. Then, create a new Expo project called "ClassAlarm":

```powershell
npx create-expo-app ClassAlarm
```

3. After the project is created, navigate into the project directory:

```powershell
cd ClassAlarm
```

4. Install the required dependencies:

```powershell
npm install @expo-google-fonts/inter expo-font expo-router @react-native-async-storage/async-storage @react-native-community/datetimepicker lucide-react-native expo-notifications expo-splash-screen
```

5. Start the development server:

```powershell
npx expo start
```

Make sure to run each command separately and wait for each one to complete before running the next one. The commands should be entered exactly as shown, without any additional text or characters.

If you're still having issues, you might want to try:

1. Using the Expo Go app on your mobile device to scan a QR code from the Expo website
2. Using Expo Snack (https://snack.expo.dev/) to create and run a project directly in your browser
3. Checking if there's a GitHub repository or ZIP file for the project that you can download

